<item>
            <title>[LU-1108] &apos;configure&apos; incorrectly set HAVE_RDMA_CREATE_ID_4ARG to 1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1108</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Building of lustre-2.1.1 rc2 failed in configuration stage with errors:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;configure:9856: result: no&lt;br/&gt;
configure:9863: error: can&apos;t compile with OpenIB gen2 headers under /usr/src/ofa_kernel-lustre211&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The configuration log &apos;config.log&apos; is attached. The configure command as shown in log is:&lt;br/&gt;
$ ./configure --enable-ext4 --disable-liblustre --with-o2ib=/usr/src/ofa_kernel-lustre211 --with-linux=/usr/src/kernels/2.6.32-220.4.1.el6.20120130.x86_64.lustre211 --with-downstream-release=0.2nasS_ofed154&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &amp;lt;rdma/rdma_cm.h&amp;gt; from rhel6.2 contains rdma_create_id prototype with 4 arguments, but the rdma_cm.h from ofed 1.5.4.1 contains rdma_create_id prototype with 3 arguments. I believe the headers from ofed should take precedence over the one from kernel. &quot;Configure&quot; failed in my case because it was incorrectly determined to set HAVE_RDMA_CREATE_ID_4ARG to 1.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
                <environment>rhel 6.2 kernel&lt;br/&gt;
ofed kernel 1.5.4.1&lt;br/&gt;
wc-release b2_1</environment>
